1
00:00:01,459 --> 00:00:02,961
- [Mel] <i>It's done.</i>
- [Erica] <i>I'm so proud of you.</i>

2
00:00:05,547 --> 00:00:08,842
<i>What made you decide</i>
<i>to finally put out the videos?</i>

3
00:00:08,925 --> 00:00:11,136
<i>Louisa. I had a dream about her.</i>

4
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:14,848
<i>She told me to… let it all fall apart.</i>

5
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:16,391
<i>Then, just start over.</i>

6
00:00:16,474 --> 00:00:18,810
<i>About Lucas and me…</i>

7
00:00:18,893 --> 00:00:19,936
<i>What I said was true.</i>

8
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:22,689
<i>Lucas will always be that one light</i>

9
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:24,941
<i>during the darkest time of my life.</i>

10
00:00:25,024 --> 00:00:26,776
<i>He made everything bearable.</i>

11
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:29,320
<i>As for what you had together, Erica.</i>
<i>Yours was cut short.</i>

12
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:32,782
<i>So, if you think this is</i>
<i>the right time for both of you,</i>

13
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:33,908
<i>I'll be fine with it.</i>

14
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:35,493
<i>Sir, I beg you.</i>

15
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:36,786
<i>I need protection!</i>

16
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:39,330
<i>We will put</i>
<i>you under our protective custody.</i>

17
00:00:39,414 --> 00:00:42,250
<i>But, that's if you</i>
<i>give us good information.</i>

18
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:44,252
<i>Lost beauty queens.</i>

19
00:00:57,182 --> 00:01:02,979
[ominous music playing]

20
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:20,872
[ominous music continues]

21
00:01:39,849 --> 00:01:45,939
[music becomes sinister]

22
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:57,200
[theme music playing]

23
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:09,063
He said all the bodies of the women

24
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:10,565
were dumped in Lake Altares?

25
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:12,150
Yes.

26
00:03:12,817 --> 00:03:14,027
But there's a problem.

27
00:03:14,694 --> 00:03:18,573
We've received the DNA results
of the bodies recovered from the lake.

28
00:03:18,948 --> 00:03:22,243
I've also sent a request
to the forensic department

29
00:03:22,327 --> 00:03:25,580
to expedite the processing
due to the urgency of the case.

30
00:03:25,663 --> 00:03:27,457
They were all accounted for…

31
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:29,125
except for one.

32
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:31,794
Francine…

33
00:03:32,754 --> 00:03:34,172
Francine Valmoria.

34
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:39,928
[uneasy music playing]

35
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:41,137
Janina Locsin.

36
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:44,015
She was shot in the head…

37
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:46,184
and dumped in the lake.

38
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:49,812
As for LJ…

39
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:51,481
she was stabbed in the front and the back

40
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:52,732
and also dumped in the lake.

41
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:13,753
[music becomes tense]

42
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:16,673
[clears throat]

43
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:19,175
Francine Valmoria.

44
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,718
She was stabbed in the back

45
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:22,345
and dumped in Lake Altares, too.

46
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,348
[sighs heavily]

47
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,101
[clears throat]

48
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:31,271
[photos tapping]

49
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:35,024
[investigator] <i>Watch him closely.</i>

50
00:04:36,025 --> 00:04:37,527
Wait, did you notice that?

51
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:39,737
What?

52
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:45,576
When it came to Francine,
he suddenly changed.

53
00:04:46,744 --> 00:04:49,205
He just looked at
the photos of the other women.

54
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:52,792
But when he saw Francine,
he picked it up.

55
00:04:53,251 --> 00:04:56,254
There was also something different
about how he talked about Francine.

56
00:04:57,213 --> 00:04:58,256
You're right.

57
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:00,675
But why the sudden change?

58
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:02,844
[Marco sighs heavily]

59
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,723
<i>This was the last message</i>
<i>exchange I had with my daughter</i>

60
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:08,141
<i>before she went missing.</i>

61
00:05:08,224 --> 00:05:09,600
<i>I can't contact her anymore.</i>

62
00:05:10,935 --> 00:05:13,604
[Erica] Francine's father suspects

63
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:15,606
that she had a
relationship with Laurence Kyo.

64
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:18,359
But Francine never admitted it.

65
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:20,361
What if…

66
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:22,030
it wasn't Kyo?

67
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:25,283
What if the guy she was in
a relationship with was Oslo?

68
00:05:27,618 --> 00:05:29,120
Do you remember that picture…

69
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:31,914
where Francine was looking at him?

70
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:35,126
[breathes deeply]

71
00:05:35,626 --> 00:05:36,627
[Marco] It is different.

72
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:39,839
If they were really in a relationship,

73
00:05:40,965 --> 00:05:42,967
it's possible
that Francine is somewhere else.

74
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:46,679
He could have done
something different with her body.

75
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:50,808
We need to find her.

76
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:53,978
I promised to bring
her back to her father.

77
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:03,362
You were in a relationship
with Francine Valmoria, right?

78
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:04,447
Where is she?

79
00:06:05,239 --> 00:06:06,824
I don't know what you're talking about!

80
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:08,951
Her body wasn't in Lake Altares!

81
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:10,119
Where is she?

82
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:12,121
- [sighs heavily]
- Are you going to confess?

83
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:15,208
Or should I revoke your immunity
so you'll end up here in jail?

84
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,335
Answer me!

85
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:20,379
PBI! We have a search warrant!

86
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:25,927
[suspenseful music playing]

87
00:06:36,145 --> 00:06:37,146
This is PBI!

88
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:40,858
[music fades]

89
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:47,532
[unsettling music playing]

90
00:07:00,294 --> 00:07:01,587
She's still alive.

91
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,714
She's still alive! Call the medic, quick!

92
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:06,759
Francine? Francine? Francine?

93
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:11,806
[music fades]

94
00:07:12,765 --> 00:07:15,643
[Greg] My poor daughter…

95
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:21,566
[sobbing, sniffling]

96
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:22,692
My dear!

97
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:24,986
My dear…

98
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:27,613
What did they do to you?

99
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,615
Don't worry, Daddy is here now.

100
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:32,535
Daddy?

101
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:35,079
Yes, this is Daddy.

102
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:36,873
It's Daddy.

103
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:40,460
My dear… My dear…

104
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:43,296
[investigator]
In our daily ops and encounters,

105
00:07:44,213 --> 00:07:46,924
moments like this remind
us that miracles do happen.

106
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,677
We were expecting to find a corpse,

107
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:53,181
but that woman turned out
to be a fighter, attorney.

108
00:07:54,056 --> 00:07:57,143
For three months,
she was chained and locked in that room.

109
00:07:57,226 --> 00:08:00,188
For three months,
she was beaten up and raped repeatedly.

110
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:02,940
For three months,
she wasn't treated as a human.

111
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:05,109
And now, you're telling me

112
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:07,737
that demon Oslo won't be sent to jail?

113
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:12,200
We found Francine
because of our deal with Oslo.

114
00:08:12,658 --> 00:08:14,118
He will be an eyewitness.

115
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:15,203
And please…

116
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:16,787
don't worry.

117
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:19,040
I will make sure
that Francine will receive

118
00:08:19,123 --> 00:08:20,958
all the help she needs.

119
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:23,586
Therapy, security details…

120
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:24,921
That's nowhere near enough!

121
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:26,714
Do you really think she'll be at peace

122
00:08:26,797 --> 00:08:30,343
knowing that the man
who violated her is not in jail…

123
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,929
and is even protected by the government?

124
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:36,390
[scoffs] We need
that demon you're criticizing!

125
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:40,311
We need him to catch even bigger demons!

126
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:42,146
It's hard to accept,

127
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,940
but this is what we need to do!

128
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:46,526
You know how things work.

129
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:48,861
You're a lawyer.

130
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:53,449
[tense music playing]

131
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:56,244
You're right.

132
00:08:57,411 --> 00:08:58,454
I know that.

133
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:02,917
But sometimes,
it's just so hard to accept.

134
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:16,639
- [car door closes]
- [indistinct chatter]

135
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:18,349
Please stay back. You're not allowed here.

136
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:19,934
- Excuse me.
- This is a restricted area.

137
00:09:20,017 --> 00:09:21,477
They found a body?

138
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:23,521
[music fades]

139
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:25,773
[Locsin] It's already decomposing,
so it's hard to identify.

140
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:27,608
But one of the hands was cut off.

141
00:09:28,317 --> 00:09:30,069
[ominous music sting]

142
00:09:30,152 --> 00:09:32,613
[unsettling music playing]

143
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:34,031
That's Esther.

144
00:09:37,952 --> 00:09:39,954
My brother killed
her nephew and her sister

145
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:42,039
in order to find out where she was hiding.

146
00:09:42,123 --> 00:09:43,374
[Esther] <i>Stay away.</i>

147
00:09:43,457 --> 00:09:44,417
[Edong] <i>Come here.</i>

148
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,294
[Esther groaning]

149
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:49,130
I guess he succeeded.

150
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:50,881
[man] What happened?

151
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,466
[cop] You're not allowed here.

152
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:54,510
[woman] Who could it be?

153
00:09:56,053 --> 00:09:58,014
[unsettling music continues]

154
00:09:58,097 --> 00:09:59,432
[exhales sharply] He did this on purpose.

155
00:10:01,892 --> 00:10:03,811
He intentionally buried Esther here…

156
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,813
to rub it in our face

157
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:09,650
that he won't let our dream
of growing old together come true!

158
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:12,445
[breathing heavily]

159
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:29,629
[sinister music sting]

160
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:33,007
[unsettling music continues, fades]

161
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:35,343
[Erica] Kyo accused Francine
and the other beauty queens

162
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:38,304
of leaving the group
and joining the enemy.

163
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:41,432
No wonder he wanted
to get rid of all of them.

164
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:49,273
[Erica] Mr. Valmoria.

165
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:50,650
Attorney.

166
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:51,692
How is she?

167
00:10:52,109 --> 00:10:54,028
Uh, the doctors said…

168
00:10:54,445 --> 00:10:55,655
she was severely dehydrated

169
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:59,241
and her wounds had
to be treated to avoid infection.

170
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,786
She's currently getting
checked for internal infection.

171
00:11:01,869 --> 00:11:03,037
They said…

172
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:05,373
her body will be able to handle it.

173
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:10,544
Attorney, because of you,
my daughter can recover.

174
00:11:13,506 --> 00:11:15,841
We should've found her sooner.

175
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:17,885
What matters is
you've successfully found her.

176
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,930
You've brought my daughter back to me.

177
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:25,976
Attorney, can I hug you?

178
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:31,148
[melancholic music playing]

179
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:34,819
[Greg sobbing, sniffling]

180
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:36,612
I'm sure…

181
00:11:36,695 --> 00:11:38,697
your parents are so proud of you.

182
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:41,033
Even someone like me,
who isn't related to you,

183
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:43,202
is so proud of you, Attorney.

184
00:11:43,285 --> 00:11:48,290
[melancholic music continues]

185
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:52,128
"SHE SAID THE SEX VIDEO WAS A DEEPFAKE.

186
00:11:52,211 --> 00:11:55,131
BUT THAT ONE WASN'T?
WHO ARE YOU TRYING TO FOOL, MEL?"

187
00:11:55,214 --> 00:12:00,094
[melancholic music continues]

188
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:21,532
"WE NEVER REALLY KNOW WHAT PEOPLE
ARE GOING THROUGH BEHIND CLOSED DOORS.

189
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:23,242
ANTON DESERVES TO BE IN JAIL!"

190
00:12:25,911 --> 00:12:28,414
"WE LOVE YOU, MEL! WE SUPPORT YOU!"

191
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:31,792
"WE WILL PRAY FOR YOUR HEALING.

192
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:35,463
WHAT YOU'RE GOING THROUGH IS NOT EASY,
BUT YOU'LL GET THROUGH IT."

193
00:12:35,546 --> 00:12:38,340
"BELIEVE WOMEN, GUYS!"

194
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:40,551
"AT LEAST, NOW, WE ARE
SEEING ANTON'S TRUE COLORS!

195
00:12:40,634 --> 00:12:42,136
GO, GO, GO, MEL!"

196
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:53,189
[melancholic music continues]

197
00:13:07,161 --> 00:13:09,997
Well, at least,
not everyone is against me.

198
00:13:10,539 --> 00:13:12,458
A lot of people are on your side, sweetie.

199
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:16,378
[melancholic music continues]

200
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:19,798
[inhales, exhales deeply]

201
00:13:21,675 --> 00:13:22,885
[sniffles]

202
00:13:33,437 --> 00:13:34,647
What happened?

203
00:13:34,730 --> 00:13:36,398
Is it true that they found a body?

204
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:38,108
It's Esther's.

205
00:13:38,776 --> 00:13:40,194
Edong buried her there.

206
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:43,822
[ominous music plays, fades]

207
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:47,076
Millette, I told you,
those videos are not real!

208
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,953
My son is not abusive!

209
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:50,871
Why?

210
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:54,708
Did I force you to drop Mel
from Grace & Glam's campaign?!

211
00:13:54,792 --> 00:13:56,418
That was your decision!

212
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:00,464
A bad look, huh?

213
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:02,049
You know what's a bad look?

214
00:14:02,132 --> 00:14:05,094
Suddenly withdrawing
your support for my son!

215
00:14:05,177 --> 00:14:07,680
And you call yourself family friends?!

216
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:09,390
[phone thuds]

217
00:14:11,392 --> 00:14:12,268
[Anton] Hmm…

218
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:15,521
You stop drinking and fix this!

219
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:18,566
They want to drop us?

220
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:20,568
Let them.

221
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:23,779
They'll regret it once I win the case.

222
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:25,531
And believe me, Ma…

223
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,658
I will win.

224
00:14:27,741 --> 00:14:28,951
[exhales heavily]

225
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:32,162
You…

226
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:34,582
After Mel release those videos,

227
00:14:34,665 --> 00:14:36,792
you're still that confident?!

228
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:38,627
I…

229
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:41,964
always win.

230
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:44,758
[unsettling music playing]

231
00:14:44,842 --> 00:14:46,010
[Barbara sighs]

232
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:49,847
Oh, Attorney.

233
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:54,351
Mr. Montenegro,

234
00:14:54,435 --> 00:14:55,644
Mrs. Montenegro.

235
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:58,731
I'm sorry,
but you need to vacate this place now.

236
00:14:58,814 --> 00:14:59,773
What?!

237
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:03,068
The family court just
granted Ms. Montenegro

238
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:04,445
a temporary protection order.

239
00:15:04,528 --> 00:15:08,407
One of the TPO's conditions is the
exclusive possession of the conjugal home.

240
00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:11,118
But we bought this house together!

241
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:12,453
It doesn't matter.

242
00:15:12,536 --> 00:15:13,996
Regardless of ownership,

243
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:17,291
the family court will require you
to leave the home immediately.

244
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:21,337
And expect restrictions on
some of your bank accounts and assets.

245
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:22,713
What the hell?

246
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:24,506
Family court?

247
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:25,758
Fuck that!

248
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:27,593
I'm not leaving my house!

249
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:29,011
This is nonnegotiable.

250
00:15:29,511 --> 00:15:31,597
If you don't comply
with the court's order,

251
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:32,932
that's a criminal offense.

252
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:34,016
You could be arrested.

253
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:35,267
Is that what you want?

254
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:37,102
[huffing] You're fucking useless!

255
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:40,022
[music fades]

256
00:15:53,410 --> 00:15:54,370
[scoffs]

257
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:57,289
[chuckles]

258
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:01,835
[laughs]

259
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:06,590
[huffs]

260
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:09,385
[sobs softly]

261
00:16:15,265 --> 00:16:16,767
If you think I'm losing it,

262
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:18,310
you're right.

263
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:21,355
[soft music playing]

264
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:22,439
[scoffs]

265
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:24,900
It's like…

266
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:29,154
the pent-up tears from
all those years I didn't cry

267
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:31,073
are about to burst out.

268
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:33,450
All of them, these last few weeks.

269
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:35,911
[exhales heavily]

270
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:40,499
[sentimental music continues]

271
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:42,376
[both sigh]

272
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:45,504
Why can't you take this as a win?

273
00:16:48,298 --> 00:16:50,426
Can't you just be proud of yourself?

274
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:54,638
Think of all the people you've helped.

275
00:16:55,472 --> 00:16:57,474
Francine, Greg…

276
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:00,477
Me.

277
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:05,274
[sentimental music swells]

278
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:11,905
Do you ever feel like…

279
00:17:14,992 --> 00:17:16,869
you're living on borrowed time?

280
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:26,378
That you've got what you have,
at the cost of others.

281
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:31,508
That at any time,
it could all just fall apart.

282
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:35,971
[sentimental music continues]

283
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:40,225
So I don't have the right to

284
00:17:40,976 --> 00:17:43,645
hold on to anything or anyone.

285
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:52,196
Is that why you avoid
getting attached to anyone?

286
00:17:55,866 --> 00:17:57,367
Like Alice said,

287
00:18:00,037 --> 00:18:01,455
we all need therapy.

288
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:03,290
[chuckles softly]

289
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:04,333
You know,

290
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:09,254
if you think you deserve
all the pain Edong has caused you,

291
00:18:09,338 --> 00:18:13,258
then remember, you also
deserve the good things in your life.

292
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:20,474
[sentimental music swells]

293
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:23,018
[cell phone chimes]

294
00:18:24,978 --> 00:18:26,605
[music fades]

295
00:18:28,232 --> 00:18:30,609
"THEY FOUND ESTHER'S BODY.
IT'S IN AMURAO."

296
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:35,781
[unsettling music playing]

297
00:18:54,758 --> 00:18:58,929
[music turns sinister]

298
00:19:03,642 --> 00:19:06,061
[grunts angrily, breathes heavily]

299
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:08,397
[high-pitched ringing]

300
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,065
[grunts angrily]

301
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:11,441
[flesh squelches]

302
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:15,904
[high-pitched ringing continues]

303
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:19,867
- [screams]
- [vase shatters]

304
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:21,952
[huffs, grunts]

305
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:24,246
[grunting angrily]

306
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:25,664
- [grunts]
- [Christina] <i>Help…</i>

307
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,042
<i>Help me…</i>

308
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:32,629
Help…

309
00:19:34,715 --> 00:19:35,716
Help.

310
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:39,845
Help.

311
00:19:41,388 --> 00:19:42,556
[weakly] Help me.

312
00:19:44,558 --> 00:19:45,642
[whimpers]

313
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:50,647
[sinister music continues]

314
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:01,742
[chains rattle]

315
00:20:12,544 --> 00:20:13,587
[lock clicks]

316
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:19,218
[sinister music continues]

317
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:28,936
[music turns suspenseful]

318
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:35,067
<i>- Come on!</i>
<i>- You're it!</i>

319
00:20:35,651 --> 00:20:38,278
<i>- No!</i>
<i>- You're it! You're it!</i>

320
00:20:38,362 --> 00:20:40,197
[kids squealing, laughing]

321
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,908
<i>- Stop it!</i>
<i>- Tag! You're it!</i>

322
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:44,493
<i>Come on!</i>

323
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:47,663
<i>You're it!</i>

324
00:20:47,746 --> 00:20:51,875
[sinister music resumes]

325
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:13,397
[sinister music continues]

326
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:20,445
[door creaks]

327
00:21:23,156 --> 00:21:24,658
[music fades]

328
00:21:24,741 --> 00:21:25,867
Uncle Edward?

329
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:27,661
[unsettling music playing]

330
00:21:27,744 --> 00:21:28,870
Auntie Christina?

331
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:30,789
- Auntie?!
- [Christina] <i>Help.</i>

332
00:21:31,915 --> 00:21:33,250
- Auntie?
- [weakly] Help…

333
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:34,960
- Auntie, what happened?
- Help me.

334
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:38,255
- Aunty Christina, where's Edward?
- Help me.

335
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:39,756
Help.

336
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,508
Auntie, sorry. Just wait a second?

337
00:21:41,591 --> 00:21:43,093
Help me.

338
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:45,304
Help.

339
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:47,014
I'll be right back, Auntie.

340
00:21:47,097 --> 00:21:48,307
[Christina] Help.

341
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:54,521
[sinister music resumes]

342
00:22:13,915 --> 00:22:20,088
[sinister music continues]

343
00:22:28,346 --> 00:22:29,389
[lock clicks]

344
00:22:45,947 --> 00:22:47,449
[tense music sting]

345
00:22:47,532 --> 00:22:52,996
[sinister music intensifies]

346
00:22:58,502 --> 00:23:02,672
[unsettling music playing]

347
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:04,591
<i>I hope you like my gift.</i>

348
00:23:04,674 --> 00:23:06,134
[gasps, whimpers]

349
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:08,303
<i>My husband's not a murderer!</i>

350
00:23:08,386 --> 00:23:09,971
- [Erica] <i>Beth, calm down.</i>
<i>- How can I calm down?</i>

351
00:23:10,055 --> 00:23:12,015
<i>They're arresting my husband!</i>
<i>He's innocent!</i>

352
00:23:12,099 --> 00:23:16,103
<i>You will suffer</i>
<i>the way I have suffered before.</i>

353
00:23:16,186 --> 00:23:17,854
<i>You're a monster!</i> [sobs]

354
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:19,314
- [Edong laughs]
<i>- What more do you want, Edong?!</i>

355
00:23:19,397 --> 00:23:21,483
<i>Let's end this!</i>

356
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:26,363
[Edong] <i>I won't stop until I destroy</i>
<i>everything you're protecting.</i>

357
00:23:26,446 --> 00:23:27,948
<i>It's payback time.</i>

358
00:23:28,031 --> 00:23:29,241
[Anton] <i>You know what's a great idea?</i>

359
00:23:29,324 --> 00:23:30,951
<i>Let's team up.</i>

360
00:23:31,034 --> 00:23:32,410
<i>We can work together.</i>

361
00:23:32,494 --> 00:23:34,287
<i>I can hurt her friends as well.</i>

362
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:36,665
[both laugh]
